==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in [[w:1822|1822]], from [[Greek]] ''δημοτικος ([[demotikos]])'' ''common, vulgar'', from Greek '' δημος ([[demos]])'' ''common people."

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-notcomp}}

# Of or for the common people.
# Of, relating to, or written in the vulgar form of ancient [[Egyptian]] [[hieratic]] writing.
#:''demotic script'' is a simplified, cursive form of [[hieroglyph]]s used in ancient egypt.
# Of, relating to, or written in the form of modern [[vernacular]] Greek.
#:''demotic Greek''

